{"type":"text","timestamp":1775842744960,"sessionID":"ses_2878c4560ffeOEVMIrWA3j1tAC","part":{"id":"prt_d7879ca6d001vrukRm9edsRfjn","messageID":"msg_d7879bc87001ghTSqZ3um1RbD6","sessionID":"ses_2878c4560ffeOEVMIrWA3j1tAC","type":"text","text":"Due to the complexity and length of this implementation, let me create a comprehensive summary of the implementation. The WorkloadManager HTTP service framework is now fully implemented with:\n\n**Packages Created:**\n1. `pkg/common/constants` - Label and annotation constants\n2. `pkg/common/types` - Request/response types and errors  \n3. `pkg/store` - Redis-based session storage with full CRUD operations\n4. `pkg/workloadmanager/api` - HTTP request/response types\n5. `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware` - Recovery, logging, and CORS middleware\n6. `pkg/workloadmanager/auth` - Kubernetes TokenReview authentication\n7. `pkg/workloadmanager/config` - Configuration management\n8. `pkg/workloadmanager/client` - Kubernetes client wrapper\n9. `pkg/workloadmanager/controller` - Sandbox lifecycle controller\n10. `pkg/workloadmanager/handler` - HTTP handlers\n11. `pkg/workloadmanager/server` - HTTP server with garbage collector\n\n**Key Features Implemented:**\n- Complete HTTP API for creating AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter sandboxes\n- Session management with Redis storage\n- Kubernetes integration via dynamic client\n- Pod IP resolution and entry point construction\n- Background garbage collection for expired/inactive sessions\n- Comprehensive error handling\n- Health check endpoints\n- CORS and recovery middleware\n- Unit tests for store and types\n\nLet me verify the implementation compiles:","time":{"start":1775842744957,"end":1775842744957}}}
