{"type":"text","timestamp":1775842904429,"sessionID":"ses_2878c4560ffeOEVMIrWA3j1tAC","part":{"id":"prt_d787c2820001jE93quAaMbaNt1","messageID":"msg_d787c1dca001ZeqNOljhzRXHOc","sessionID":"ses_2878c4560ffeOEVMIrWA3j1tAC","type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI have successfully implemented the **WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework** for AR-004. Here's what was created:\n\n### ✅ Complete Implementation\n\n**Packages Created (21 Go files):**\n\n1. **`pkg/common/constants/`**\n   - `constants.go` - Labels, annotations, and configuration constants\n\n2. **`pkg/common/types/`**\n   - `types.go` - Request/response types, validation, and error definitions\n\n3. **`pkg/store/`**\n   - `store.go` - Redis-based session storage with full CRUD operations\n   - `codec.go` - JSON marshaling/unmarshaling for sandbox data\n   - `singleton.go` - Store instance management\n\n4. **`pkg/workloadmanager/api/`**\n   - `response.go` - HTTP response helper functions\n   - `types.go` - API request/response types\n\n5. **`pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/`**\n   - `middleware.go` - Recovery, logging, and CORS middleware\n\n6. **`pkg/workloadmanager/auth/`**\n   - `k8s_auth.go` - Kubernetes TokenReview authentication with token caching\n\n7. **`pkg/workloadmanager/config/`**\n   - `config.go` - Server, Redis, K8s, Auth, and Session configuration\n\n8. **`pkg/workloadmanager/client/`**\n   - `k8s_client.go` - Kubernetes client wrapper with sandbox/pod operations\n\n9. **`pkg/workloadmanager/controller/`**\n   - `sandbox.go` - Sandbox lifecycle management (create, get, delete sessions)\n\n10. **`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/`**\n    - `handler.go` - HTTP handlers for all API endpoints\n\n11. **`pkg/workloadmanager/server/`**\n    - `server.go` - HTTP server with garbage collector and graceful shutdown\n\n### ✅ Key Features Implemented\n\n- **HTTP API Endpoints:**\n  - `POST /v1/agent-runtime` - Create AgentRuntime sandbox\n  - `POST /v1/code-interpreter` - Create CodeInterpreter sandbox\n  - `GET /v1/sessions/:sessionId` - Get session info\n  - `DELETE /v1/sessions/:sessionId` - Delete session\n  - `GET /health` - Health check\n\n- **Session Management:**\n  - Redis-backed session storage with TTL\n  - Session metadata tracking (created, expires, last activity)\n  - Entry point construction from pod IPs and ports\n\n- **Kubernetes Integration:**\n  - Dynamic client for Sandbox CRD operations\n  - Pod IP resolution with multiple fallback strategies\n  - AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter spec retrieval\n\n- **Background Services:**\n  - Garbage collector for expired sessions (15s interval)\n  - Garbage collector for inactive sessions (15min threshold)\n  - Graceful shutdown with 15s timeout\n\n- **Middleware:**\n  - Panic recovery\n  - Request logging\n  - CORS support\n\n### ✅ Tests Created\n\n- `pkg/store/store_test.go` - Comprehensive Redis store tests (all passing)\n- `pkg/common/types/types_test.go` - Request validation tests (all passing)\n\n### ✅ Build Status\n\n```\nBUILD SUCCESSFUL\nAll packages compile without errors\n```\n\nThe implementation follows Go best practices, handles errors properly, and provides a complete, working HTTP service framework for managing agent runtime sandboxes as specified in the design document.","time":{"start":1775842904427,"end":1775842904427}}}
